gujarati.context:
Here is the translation:

This time a strange person appeared, Mohan's face seen; 
After that from there went away happily, became what was to be, so war ended.

Here is the translation:

He felt a bond with joined hands, then left without going; 
I came to one cave forest, stayed sleepless there homeless.

This is what I got:

It's like fate is waiting for Bhuvah, I am pleased in my mind with whatever has to happen now; 
Others have come in Hari's way, thus they are helping the devotee.

Chali baay ne kaadiya bahaar, diyae thapako vaarmaavaar;
Havu kari shema aavun phari, em kahine sadaavya hari.

Here is the translation:

I shall take away from my side what is outside, as long as it pleases God; 
Now I shall go with my own accord, as per God's will.

Here is the translation:

I left it in the house, kept it securely, to be kept; 
Those from my place took away the valuables, those things were made useless and remained like that.
